args: Did you want these sunflowers placed\nin front of the store, ma'am?
Yes, that will be perfect. Thank you again\nfor helping me tidy everything up.
It finally looks fit to open up shop.\nShould be able to do business as\nusual tomorrow!
I cannot thank you all enough. But...
Is something wrong? You don't look happy.
Well, my shop may be back to normal,\nbut I don't know how many people\nwill want to come here regardless.
Ever since the fiends attacked, more and\nmore people have been leaving town.
Yeah, but I can't really blame 'em.\nFiends are enough to make most folks\nturn tail and never look back.
I suppose it is normal in such situations to\nwant to go somewhere one can feel safe.
I have no intention of leaving this town,\nbut it saddens me to see everyone do so.
Also, I'm not sure the ones who remain\nare in the mood for appreciating flowers.
There must be something we can—
Hey, sorry for buttin' in all unannounced\nand junk. I'm Natalie—a festival planner.
The hell is a festival planner?

We organize festivals, duh-doy!
Basically we plan 'em all out,
decide what's gonna happen when,
and then make sure it does.
Okay. But how's a festival gonna help this\nhere lady with her broke flower shop?
If we liven up the town with a festival,\neveryone in it will cheer up, too!
Can something so simple truly work?
I've seen this happen in more towns\nthan you can count, lady.

And wow, I gotta say, the flowers in this
shop are great! I bet we could use 'em
to make a big fancy decoration for
the festival.
Are ya really gonna stand here and\norganize a festival all on yer own?
Of course not—I'll need all of\nthe townspeople to chip in.
But if I can show 'em MY enthusiasm,\nthat'll make 'em more likely to help.
I gotta make 'em WANT a festival!
Heh. I like the way ya think, kid.
Taking action is always commendable,\nso long as the plan is sound.
Aw, I'm gonna start blushin' over here.
Listen up, flower lady: I'm gonna bring\nlife back to this town. You can count on it!
So just hang in there, yeah?
Well, this sounds like a wonderful plan!\nAnd please feel free to use my flowers\nin any ways that you might need.
Right then! Time to track down the mayor\nof this joint and get him to sign the\npermission forms or whatever.
...Hey, so why're you guys still\nfollowin' me around?
You ain't been in town more than\na hot second, yeah?
Figured we'd show ya where\nthe mayor's place was.
Eh, don't mention it. You seem like a\ngood kid, and this festival thingie\nkinda has me excited.
Still, if we might ask, why did you\ncome to this town in the first place?
Oh, yeah. So, my partner and I got\nseparated during our travels.
I got wind he's in this town,\nbut I just can't find the guy.
Then should you not be searching for him\ninstead of planning an event?
Nah. Soon as I start preppin' for a festival,\nhe'll pop his ugly mug outta the ground.
How can you be so certain?
'Cause he's a festival planner like me.\nAnd once he sees this sad sack town,\nhe's gonna want to throw one here.
Hell, he's probably plannin' it already.
He sounds like an interesting fellow.\nYou must really trust him.
I trust that his head is empty of anythin'\n'cept festivals.
Not that I'm a whole lot different.\nWe both believe in the power of festivals!
Don't matter HOW gloomy a town is—\na festival will set it on its feet again.
If we can't even do that, we oughta quit\nour jobs and go farm potatoes!
I'm likin' ya more by the minute, kid!\nThink it's time what ya meet the prince.
...Well, speak of the man himself!\nGreat timin', {player_name}!
There he is! Where the hell\nhave you BEEN, Yaten?!
You're here just in time, Natalie.\nBecause guess what...
Why'd you say the same thing as me?
Guess we're just on the same wavelength.
Well, you're right—the boss man here\nasked me to throw together a festival.
Then let's make it a festival these\nfolks ain't never gonna forget!
Hello there. I take it you are\na festival planner like Yaten?
If so, we'd really appreciate your help\nin restoring some life to this town.
You got it, Princey. Oh, and the name's\nNatalie—it's great to meet ya!
